lead_paragraph: A letter published in the San Francisco Curier from Col. REDICK McKEE chief of the Indian Commission. states that treaties had been concluded with eight tribes in the vicinity of Clear Lake, and that four tribes on the Russian river were about signing similar bonds of peace and friendship.
